---
import { Image } from "astro:assets"
import me from '../../public/its-me.jpg'
import myVenmo from '../../public/my-venmo.jpg'
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
		<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Young+Serif&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
		<title>Make Richie Rich</title>
	</head>
	<body>
	<section class="bg-slate-100 lg:bg-white py-[60px] lg:py-[120px] flex flex-col items-center justify-center">
		<div class="container px-6 mx-auto text-center">
			<h1 class="text-2xl lg:text-5xl"><span class="text-green-500 text-2xl">$$$</span> Make Richie Rich <span class="text-green-500 text-2xl">$$$</span></h1>
			<div class="flex-col lg:flex-row justify-center flex gap-10 mt-12">
				<div class="p-6 bg-white shadow-2xl rounded-xl">
					<Image src={myVenmo} alt="its me" class="h-[300px] w-full object-contain"/>
					<p class="mt-4 mb-0">Scan to gift me $1</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class="bg-white lg:bg-slate-100 py-[60px] lg:py-[120px]">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="w-full prose-sm lg:prose-lg px-6 max-w-none text-center">
			<div class="lg:py-6 lg:px-12 lg:bg-white lg:shadow-2xl lg:rounded-xl">
					<Image src={me} alt="its me" class="h-[300px] w-auto mx-auto object-contain border-2 rounded-md border-neutral-300"/>
				<h1 class="clamp">Correcting the "Richie Rich" Label</h1>
				<div class="text-justify">
					<p> I'm Richard, and let me tell you, I had this crazy belief that someday, I'd be rolling in cash, able to retire in style and enjoy a life of leisure. But here's the kicker: I couldn't stand how folks casually slapped that "Richie Rich" label on every Richard they came across. It wasn't just a nickname; it was an unfair jab that stung like lemon juice in a paper cut. The irony? I wasn't exactly rolling in the dough, and being called "Richie Rich" while struggling was like rubbing salt in the wound!</p>
					
					<p>So, I thought, "Enough is enough!" I'm gearing up to kick off a fiery social media crusade that'll rip the lid off the absurd "Richie Rich" tag. I'm about to lay down the law on how this label has perpetuated stereotypes, slapped us with impossible expectations, and painted a picture that's so far from our actual lives, it's like mistaking a zucchini for a rocket ship!</p>
					
					<p>When my campaign catches fire, folks from every nook and cranny of life will flock to my banner. They won't just be backing my cause; they'll be coughing up their "tribute" for all those times they unknowingly fueled this problem over the years. The cash will start flowing in, greasing the wheels to make my early retirement dreams more feasible than ever. It's like a tidal wave of karma, and I'm ready to ride it to financial freedom!</p>
					
					<p>I'm telling you, my message is gonna flip perceptions upside down. Regular folks and even businesses, all caught up in the momentum of my cause, will start rethinking how they label us Richards. They'll finally get that the "Richie Rich" thing is a real buzzkill.</p>
					
					<p>And you know what's crazy? If I ever managed to hit that goal of gifts and support, I'd be okay with wearing the "Richie Rich" label as a badge of honor. After all, I hustled hard, retired on my own terms, and enjoyed a life of luxury, all while putting the spotlight on how that label messed with not just my life but with a whole bunch of other Richards. My retirement? It was earned, deserved, and made the world a better place. I can finally savor the sweet taste of my dreams, knowing things have changed for the better.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	</section>
	</body>
</html>